== Installation ==

There are several options available for using Flash Player on Gentoo. Some options work with all web browsers, while others are limited to specific web browsers.

=== Adobe Flash ===

Adobe provides a Flash Player for both [[Wikipedia:NPAPI|NPAPI]]-based browsers (e.g. [[Firefox]], Konqueror) and [[Wikipedia:Google_Native_Client#PPAPI|PPAPI]]-based browsers (e.g. [[Chromium]]).

To use Flash Player with a NPAPI-based browser, enable the <code>nsplugin</code> USE flag:

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/portage/package.use|1=
www-plugins/adobe-flash nsplugin
}}

To use Flash Player with a PPAPI-based browser, enable the <code>ppapi</code> USE flag:

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/portage/package.use|1=
www-plugins/adobe-flash ppapi
}}

Flash Player has a proprietary license that needs to be accepted before installation:

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/portage/package.license|1=
www-plugins/adobe-flash AdobeFlash-11.x"
}}

Next, install Adobe Flash Player:

{{Emerge|www-plugins/adobe-flash}}

After installation, start/restart the web browser.

=== Google Chrome ===

Google [[Chrome]] bundles a [[Wikipedia:Google_Native_Client#PPAPI|PPAPI]]-based Flash Player. Simply install {{Package|www-client/google-chrome}} to use Flash Player:

{{Emerge|www-client/google-chrome}}

{{Note|This will not enable Flash Player for use in other web browsers.}}

=== freshplayerplugin ===

freshplayerplugin is a NPAPI wrapper for the PPAPI-based Flash Player. To use the PPAPI-based Flash Player with a NPAPI-based browser, install {{Package|www-plugins/freshplayerplugin}}:

{{Emerge|www-plugins/freshplayerplugin}}

After installation, start/restart the web browser.

=== Without Flash Player ===

An alternative to using Flash Player when only playing video streams from YouTube, Vimeo, Twitch, Internet TV stream, etc., is to install {{Package|media-video/mpv}} with the <code>lua</code> USE flag, and {{Package|media-video/ffmpeg}} or {{Package|media-video/libav}} with the <code>openssl</code> USE flag. The <code>lua</code> USE flag allows {{Package|net-misc/youtube-dl}} to work in mpv, and the <code>openssl</code> USE flag allows FFmpeg/Libav to open {{Path|https://}} streams. Next, install the [https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/open-with/ Open-with Firefox add-on] and configure it in the following way:

* Open {{Path|about:openwith}}, select {{Path|Add...}}
* In the dialog select a video streaming capable player (e.g. {{Path|/usr/bin/mpv}}).
* (Optional step) Choose how to display the dialogs using the left panel of Open-with add-on.
* Right click on links or visit pages containing videos. If the site is supported, the player will be open as expected.

The same procedure can be used to associate other video downloaders such as {{Package|net-misc/youtube-dl}}.

